manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Applicator free tampons for a more sustainable, plastic free choice. Just as natural as a period. Veeda Non-Applicator Tampons are made with ultra-absorbent all-natural 100% cotton for reliable, leak-proof protection. Designed with specialized grooves for added absorption and all-natural cotton string for easy removal. Available in: Lite, Regular, Super & Super Plus with Compact BPA-Free Applicator or Applicator Free Synthetic and/or scented period care products can irritate the sensitive skin of the vulva. Veeda tampons are natural, hypoallergenic and dermatologically tested, which is very important for health. In fact, statistics show that yeast infections are less likely to occur with natural products that contain no chemicals and fragrances. Our 100% natural cotton is sourced directly from a global network of leading cotton traders and all cotton is cleansed with an oxygen cleansing process, not chlorine-bleached, for a healthier eco-friendlier product. This process removes all dirt and impurities including any synthetic matter and this is the exact same process by which all organic cotton is cleansed with, to ensure it also has no synthetic substances. This ensures that the final tampons are truly 100% natural cotton. Veeda tampons are lab-tested for over 250 harmful chemicals and contain no wood or synthetic fibres, no additives, no harsh chemicals and no dioxins. Another advantage to using 100% pure, hypoallergenic cotton, is that cotton does not contribute to the growth of the bacteria that causes Toxic Shock Syndrome (TSS), irritation and allergic reactions. BETTER FOR YOU, BETTER FOR THE PLANET - Veeda tampons are made with naturally soft, absorbent 100% pure GMO-Free cotton (that’s it, nothing else!) ensuring that your body only meets with the purest, irritation free ingredients. Since 100% pure cotton is made by nature, it biodegrades by nature and won’t build up in landfill.

Tampons for Teens These ultra thin tampons are also great for teens and tweens and girls who are new to periods or new to tampons. If you're looking for junior tampons for teens, beginner tampons for teens or small tampons for teens, these non applicator tampons for teens and tweens are naturally perfect. Many of us are conscious of the ingredients in the foods we eat and the products we put on our skin and hair, choosing the hypoallergenic, organic or natural options. Yet, somehow, there is extremely low awareness among women of what ingredients are used in their sanitary protection products and what implications they may have for their health. We believe that natural products are better for you and for our planet. We also believe that when it comes to products that touch the skin, particularly in the most intimate parts of the body, it’s important to know exactly where it came from and how it got there. This is why we are committed to ensuring that all of our products contain ONLY pure, hypoallergenic, 100% natural cotton with No Nasty Chemicals and No Dyes. Unlike other brands, our cotton is grown naturally, not manufactured or altered. Plus, all our products are gently cleansed with oxygen and are chlorine-free. Conventional period care products from well-known brands can be made from blends of bleached cotton and/or synthetic products. They can also contain dioxins from the bleaching process, herbicide residues, synthetic chemicals, artificial fragrances, and dyes. We want to make sure that our products are kinder to the earth in every way possible. After learning how conventionally made feminine care products affected our body and environment, Veeda was created. The average woman uses 11,000 feminine care products in her lifetime; this fact alone keeps us inspired to create a top of line sustainable process when manufacturing our products. Veeda products are made with pure, hypoallergenic, 100% natural cotton. Our cotton is grown naturally, not manufactured or altered. Both our tampons and pads are gently cleansed with oxygen and are chlorine-free. Veeda tampons are made only with 100% Natural Cotton and have No Nasty Chemicals, No Synthetics, and No Dyes. Knowing the facts, consider making a better choice by making Veeda your go-to natural period care brand.
ABOUT VEEDA We created Veeda because you and your body deserve the best. No harsh chemicals here — just natural goodness that always goes with the flow (literally).

Better for You No Chemicals. No Synthetics. No Dyes. Our applicator-free tampons are 100% natural GMO-free cotton and hypoallergenic. Natural leak-free protection you can count on! Better for the planet Our tampons are packaged using recyclable materials. Veeda is committed to sustainably-sourced ingredients and safe manufacturing processes. Better for all We’re working to end period poverty once and for all. Every time you buy a Veeda product, you help us deliver period care essentials to those who need them the most.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not What I accepted
reviews.reviewText: I accepted these to have the applicator and there was nothing, I find it really gross to think that I wouldn't use one. I should have done more research but these just got thrown away :/

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you don’t mind not having an applicator, can recommend
reviews.reviewText: If you don’t mind not having an applicator, this could be for you. I was looking for a tampon without a natural applicator and natural cotton (not the processed stuff), and the period cup I had was not working for me because my period got lighter and got to be too much of a hassle right now.They come individually wrapped in thin plastic (so its not completely plastic free), but that’s about it. They have a string at the end so you don’t lose it in your vagina like other tampons. Honestly, only downside I see to it is that to apply it, you have to shove it in with your finger(s). I don’t mind because I don’t go to public bathrooms often, but this is something to consider.After that, pretty comfy, nice regular tampon. Works just fine lol.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Veeda improves periods!
reviews.reviewText: I read that natural cotton tampons could actually reduce cramping and bleeding – I have to say this is true! I have noticed a significant change in my cramps and flow since switching to Veeda. 100% worth it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yea! No applicator!
reviews.reviewText: Veeda tampons are my favorite. I find other tampons (even “natural” ones) irritating, but I’ve never had that problem with Veeda. I just had previously only seen them with a wasteful plastic applicator. I’m so glad to be able to buy them without an applicator. They can be discreetly carried in a change purse or pocket, and only a small amount of plastic wrapper for waste. The absorbency is equivalent to Cora or OB applicator free tampons.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best accidental order ever!
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these tampons thinking that they had applicators. They did not have applicators. But a tampon is always useful to have around & these are very compact, so I kept them. When I finally used them I was floored. They are incredibly easy to insert and take up almost no room in my purse! And one of the reasons I use Veeda is for their all natural products. The minimum packaging on this product made my inner conservationist very happy.
Great product. Easy to use. Very nice to have high quality cotton.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on June 9, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I tried these as a solution for the start of lockdown, selfish people had bought up all of the tampons in the supermarkets so I was forced to get whatever I could, they were fine as a stop gap however not particularly absorbent, I leaked quite a lot without having a particularly heavy flow... good as a stop gap, pretty expensive- 20 tampons for almost £10...
It is tiny but slightly hard to put in since I’m not a regular user, take some time. And when at the beginning of menstruation it’s little bit hard to put in without a applicator...
